		</p>
		<h2>Cookies</h2>
		<p>A cookie, as defined for this policy, is a small piece of data which is sent 
			from a web server to a web browser and stored locally on the user's machine. 
			Natural Link Exchange uses cookies to allocate short-term identification values 
			on computers that access our web servers. This ID allows us to award valid 
			sales credits to our affiliates, prevent attacks on our systems such as denial 
			of service attacks and identify and thwart fake transactions. Unless 
			specifically stated, all Natural Link Exchange cookies are: temporary, less 
			than 10KB in size, only accessible to Natural Link Exchange servers and 
			completely free of any personally identifiable information.</p>
		<h2>Security</h2>
		<p>We have implemented safeguards to protect any personally identifiable 
			information we collect about you and only store this information on servers 
			that have limited access. We keep personally identifiable information only as 
			long as required to complete a purchase or maintain a subscription, prevent 
			fraud and scams, supply customer service, or continue your account with us.</p>
